@NODE OPER "Operation"

Operation
ĮĮĮĮĮĮĮĮĮ
Double click on the PhoneProUsa icon and an information requestor will
appear. Click on Lets Go! or press enter to start PhoneProUsa.

A new window will appear with several commands listed and a text box with
the number zero in it.

To Select a mode delete the zero and type the number of your choice, if you
wish to leave PhoneProUsa then leave the zero there and hit enter or click
on Ok or Cancel.

Commands
~~~~~~~~

0 = Quit.
    Already explained.

1 = Information.
    Shows global information about PhonePro Usa.

2 = Change Screen Palette.
    Brings up a requestor to change the screen colours, click on the colour
you wish to change and move the slider of your choice to vary the amount of
red, green or blue in that shade. Selecting UNDO will revert the colour you
just changed to its previous value, and CANCEL will return to PhonePro and
not change any of the colours. Selecting OK will accept the changes you
have made to the colour palette.

3 = Vector Check.
    A simple virus scanner, this will check the areas of memory where a virus
can reside, if anything is there you will be warned in the window. A
requester will then a appear for you to proceed. 

    NOTE: Virii are NOT removed, you are only warned if there are any
memory resident programs (Cool/Cold Capture prgs, etc...).

4 = Open a Public Shell.
    A new 4 colour screen will open with an AmigaShell prompt, to exit type
Endcli. This is a public screen and utilities which support pub screens can
relocate themselves there if you tell them to move there (normally an
option in that prg). The pubscreen name is PHONEUSASCR.

    NOTE: This pubscreen shanghies all programs that are opened on the
workbench.

5 = Open Normal Shell
    This opens a QShell on the current screen that PhonePro is active on. 

    NOTE: This is actually a very dodgy QShell and the directory cannot be
changed, this will be corrected in a newer version.

6 = Show Memory
    Shows the available memory in a seperate window.

7 = Activate Sleep
    Sends PhonePro USA to sleep and can started up again by selecting
PhonePro in the Tools menu on the workbench.

